    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in New Zealand reflect the distance from major markets and high local healthcare costs:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Resident transition:</strong> Once resident, public healthcare is free</li>
    <li><strong>Southern Cross:</strong> Much cheaper than international insurance for residents</li>
    <li><strong>Higher excess:</strong> NZ$2,000+ excess reduces premiums significantly</li>
    <li><strong>ACC coverage:</strong> Remember accidents are covered regardless; focus illness coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Parent Visa Applicant, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Daughter is NZ citizen. Applying for Parent Retirement Visa with NZ$1.2M investment.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global during 4-year investment period. After residence granted, switch to public + Southern Cross.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~NZ$550/month during processing. After residence: Southern Cross ~NZ$300/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Long-Stay Visitor, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 9-month visitor visa to spend time with grandchildren. No pathway to residence.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive coverage. No public healthcare access except ACC for accidents.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~NZ$750/month. Essential for hospital care at NZ$1,500+/night private rates.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Australian Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Trans-Tasman rights allow residence in NZ. Moving to Wellington.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Immediate public healthcare access via reciprocal agreement. Add Southern Cross for elective surgery wait times.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Southern Cross ~NZ$280/month. Public care free. Keep Australian Medicare for visits home.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to New Zealand without significant wealth?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult. The Parent Retirement Visa requires NZ$1M+ investment. The Parent Resident Visa through family sponsorship has limited places and a ballot system. Without NZ citizen children or significant assets, long-term residence options are limited.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What does ACC (Accident Compensation) cover?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        ACC covers treatment for ALL accidents—car accidents, falls, sports injuries—for everyone in New Zealand, including tourists. It's a no-fault system funded by levies. This means accident-related care is largely free, but illness and disease are not covered by ACC.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does New Zealand compare to Australia for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Similar English-speaking culture and lifestyle. NZ is smaller, greener, and generally considered more relaxed. Australia has more variety of climates and cities. Immigration is difficult for both without family ties. NZ costs are lower than Australian cities like Sydney.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the time zone challenge?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        New Zealand is UTC+12/13 (depending on daylight saving). This is 17-20 hours ahead of US East Coast, 11-13 hours ahead of UK. Staying connected with family in Europe or Americas requires planning. Video calls often happen early morning NZ time or late night for family abroad.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for New Zealand.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with New Zealand immigration and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
